commText: Sai Sudharsan and Shubman Gill are at the crease. Sai Sudharsan is on strike. M Siddharth will open the attack
M Siddharth to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, and Sai Sudharsan is away, good length on the middle and leg line, flicked to deep mid-wicket
A wide slip in.
M Siddharth to Shubman Gill, no run, flat good length outside off, Shubman Gill mistimes the cut to cover-point
M Siddharth to Shubman Gill, 1 run, that one-finger swinger, the inswinger and driven hard back to M Siddharth, it bursts through his hands
M Siddharth to Sai Sudharsan, no run, good length on the middle and leg line, flicked to backward square leg
M Siddharth to Sai Sudharsan, 2 wides, tries the flat, fast arm-ball, but down leg, KL can't glove it cleanly and they take one more
M Siddharth to Shubman Gill, no run, tossed up full outside off, Shubman Gill gets forward to drive to extra-cover, straight to the fielder
M Siddharth to Shubman Gill, 1 run, flat good length and curves back in on off, punched to long-off
Naveen-ul-Haq, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Naveen-ul-Haq to Shubman Gill, 2 runs, wide of the crease and angling into middle, short of length and tucked wide of deep square leg for two
Naveen-ul-Haq to Shubman Gill, no run, wide of the crease and short of length outside off, stays a bit low, Shubman Gill cuts and misses
Naveen-ul-Haq to Shubman Gill, 1 run, short of length on off, drop and run in front of KL

Naveen-ul-Haq to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, no slip and four. Sai Sudharsan gets lucky. Fullish outside off, Sudharsan throws the bat and the thick outside-edge flies to where a 1st or 2nd slip would have been
Now a wide slip in.
Naveen-ul-Haq to Sai Sudharsan, 2 runs, fullish outside off, steered wide of deep backward point for two
Naveen-ul-Haq over the wicket.
Naveen-ul-Haq to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, beautiful shot. Full outside off, Sai Sudharsan walks into the straight drive and holds the pose to play an attractive shot. The shot of the game so far
M Siddharth to Shubman Gill, no run, good length on the stumps, punched to the left of Siddharth who gets across and cuts it off
M Siddharth to Shubman Gill, no run, wide of the crease and tossed up on leg-stump, turned to mid-wicket
M Siddharth to Shubman Gill, no run, flat good length on off, punched back
M Siddharth to Shubman Gill, 1 run, tight run and Sai Sudharsan gets there with a dive, and there's no direct-hit either, punched to cover and Padikkal was the fielder
M Siddharth to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, drifting down leg, Sai Sudharsan pulls to deep backward square leg
M Siddharth to Shubman Gill, 2 runs, drifting down leg, flicked in front of deep mid-wicket and an easy two
Mayank Yadav, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Mayank Yadav to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, 140.9kph, full outside off, Sai Sudharsan with a lovely off-drive, stays still and just a high elbow meeting the ball, so lovely to see
Mayank Yadav to Sai Sudharsan, no run, 140.6kph, bouncer and Sai Sudharsan ducks
Mayank Yadav to Sai Sudharsan, no run, 139.1kph, another bouncer and Sai Sudharsan ducks again
Mayank Yadav to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, 138.4kph, short of length on the pads, Sai Sudharsan flicks that wide of square leg and it races away, again compact batting
Mayank Yadav to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 139.1kph, short down leg, Sai Sudharsan pulls to deep backward square leg
Mayank Yadav to Shubman Gill, FOUR, 137.7kph, short and rising outside off, Shubman Gill rises on his tiptoes and flashes the cut over backward point, Mayank Yadav goes for 13 in his first over
Mayank Yadav is off. Hopefully it is nothing serious.
M Siddharth to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, back of a length on middle, Sai Sudharsan pulls to deep backward square leg

M Siddharth to Shubman Gill, no run, again confusion between Shubman Gill and Sai Sudharsan, Sai Sudharsan lucky that he got back, dives to get back in, good length outside off, punched wide of cover-point and had there been a direct-hit, Sudharsan was gone. Gill apologises immediately
M Siddharth to Shubman Gill, 1 run, good length on middle, nudged wide of mid-on
M Siddharth to Sai Sudharsan, no ball, 2 runs, poor from Siddharth, a front-foot no-ball, full on the pads, flicked wide of deep mid-wicket for two
A free-hit next.

M Siddharth to Sai Sudharsan, no ball, leg byes, 1 run, another front-foot no-ball, KL now goes to Siddharth to have a word. Full and flat on the stumps, Sai Sudharsan misses the slogsweep, but takes a legbye to short fine
Now a free-hit to Shubman Gill.
M Siddharth to Shubman Gill, no run, full outside off, driven straight to the fielder at extra-cover. A dot
M Siddharth to Shubman Gill, 1 run, good length on middle, Shubman Gill gets forward to push to long-off

M Siddharth to Sai Sudharsan, no ball, 2 runs, sloppy from LSG. First from Siddharth and then from the fielder. Driven to cover-point who lets it go through his hands, was a dot and now it's a three-run delivery, and a free-hit next
M Siddharth to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, tossed up full on off, slogged high up in the air and caught at deep mid-wicket but won't matter as it is a free-hit, Siddharth relieved that the over is done

Over Summary (1-5): -- Siddharth, the Impact Player, starts with a 5-run over -- 2 contrasting (streaky and fluent) boundaries in an over for Sai Sudharsan -- Another tidy over from Siddharth -- 13 runs (3 boundaries) off Mayank Yadav's 1st over -- Mix-up and Sai survives -- Three front-foot no-balls in an over from Siddharth (12 runs off it)
Yash Thakur, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Yash Thakur to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, short at Sai Sudharsan who mistimes the pull, goes to backward square leg
Yash Thakur to Shubman Gill, FOUR, slapped away. Shubman Gill makes room and cuts the back of a length delivery from leg-stump, wide of point

Yash Thakur to Shubman Gill, 1 run, slower short ball at Shubman Gill who pulls to deep backward square leg, a grunt of frustration from Shubman Gill after he hit that, not happy that he found the fielder
Yash Thakur to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, back of a length outside off, punched wide of mid-on
First 50-plus opening stand for GT this season.
Yash Thakur to Shubman Gill, no run, full outside off, Shubman Gill makes room and drives straight to the fielder at extra-cover
Yash Thakur to Shubman Gill, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Yash Thakur to Shubman Gill, out Bowled!! Straight through. Shubman Gill has played all around a full straight delivery, flicks and misses, was the cross-seamer and the stumps are rattled. LSG needed that wicket. It's the timeout as well. Shubman Gill b Yash Thakur 19(21) [4s-2]
LSG were under pressure and that wicket should help them get back into this. Still GT will be comfortable at the moment.
Here's GT's Impact Player Kane Williamson. He replaces Mohit Sharma
Kane Williamson, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Krunal Pandya, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Krunal Pandya to Sai Sudharsan, no run, 93.9kph, flat and quick from a short of length, patted to cover
Krunal Pandya to Sai Sudharsan, no run, appeal for lbw as Sai Sudharsan misses the clip. Probably pitched outside leg. Would have missed leg too
Krunal Pandya to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, full and quick, knocked to long-off
Krunal Pandya to Williamson, no run, 97.6kph, non-turner on the stumps, pushed back to the bowler
Krunal Pandya to Williamson, no run, 97.7kph, stump-to-stump line, defended to midwicket
Krunal Pandya to Williamson, 1 run, 99.1kph, Williamson skips down the track and turns this short of length ball to backward square leg to get off the mark. Just two runs off Pandya's opening over
Spin from both ends...
Ravi Bishnoi, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Ravi Bishnoi to Williamson, no run, 95.7kph, fullish ball drifting in, Williamson gets forward to push it back to the bowler
Ravi Bishnoi to Williamson, THATS OUT!! Caught&Bowled!!

Ravi Bishnoi to Williamson, out Caught&Bowled!! Ravi Bishnoi takes a one-handed screamer! 97.7kph, another in-drifter, fullish in length and Williamson gets forward to on-drive. Doesn't quite get to the pitch of the delivery and ends up chipping it in the air. Bishnoi flies to his right in his followthrough and sticks his right hand out to snaffle it out of thin air. Throws the ball in the air, gets up and has his arms aloft. Williamson c and b Ravi Bishnoi 1(5)
Sharath BR, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Ravi Bishnoi to Sharath BR, no run, 99.4kph, defended
Ravi Bishnoi to Sharath BR, 1 run, turned to backward square leg
Ravi Bishnoi to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 96.9kph, wrong 'un, eased to deep backward point
Ravi Bishnoi to Sharath BR, no run, 98.6kph, googly, Sharath BR gets forward to push and inside-edges it onto his pad. Excellent over from Bishnoi
Krunal Pandya to Sai Sudharsan, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Krunal Pandya to Sai Sudharsan, out Caught by Ravi Bishnoi!! Holes out! 100.3kph, short of length, Sai Sudharsan rocks back to pull and loses his shape in the process. Bit of extra bounce and he top-edges it to deep midwicket where Bishnoi takes a safe catch. GT have lost their top three within a span of 14 deliveries. Game on! Sai Sudharsan c Ravi Bishnoi b Krunal Pandya 31(23) [4s-4]
Vijay Shankar, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Krunal Pandya to Shankar, 1 run, 98.7kph, in-dart on middle and leg, Shankar closes his bat-face to tuck it to backward square leg

Krunal Pandya to Sharath BR, 1 run, 83.5kph, gives a bit of air on this occasion does Pandya and gets it to grip. Sharath BR pokes tentatively and the ball rolls towards short third man off the outside edge
Krunal Pandya to Shankar, 1 run, 98.4kph, punched to long-off
Krunal Pandya to Sharath BR, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Krunal Pandya to Sharath BR, out Caught by Ayush Badoni!! Four down! 100.6kph, fullish outside off and Sharath BR gets down low to play a premeditated sweep shot. This one might have held onto the pitch a bit. Lobs up in the air off the top-edge and Badoni comes in from deep backward square leg to gobble it up. Second wicket in the over for Krunal Pandya. Sharath BR c Ayush Badoni b Krunal Pandya 2(5)
A slip in place
Darshan Nalkande, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Krunal Pandya to Darshan Nalkande, no run, 100.5kph, in-dart on middle, Darshan Nalkande nudges it into the leg-side
In the previous over, Mayank Yadav was seen leaving the field due to side strain..
Ravi Bishnoi to Shankar, 1 run, googly, Shankar pushes with hard hands and inside-edges to backward square leg
Ravi Bishnoi to Darshan Nalkande, 1 run, 97.9kph, another wrong 'un, worked through square leg
Ravi Bishnoi to Shankar, no run, 95.7kph, googly, middle-stump line, Shankar gets forward to defend and gets an inside edge onto his pad. The ball pops up but falls well short of midwicket
Leg gully in place
Ravi Bishnoi to Shankar, 1 run, 93.9kph, touch too full from Bishnoi and that's been driven along the ground to long-off
Ravi Bishnoi to Darshan Nalkande, 1 run, 98.3kph, wrong 'un, Darshan Nalkande looks to clip it and inside-edges it wide of leg gully
Ravi Bishnoi to Shankar, wide, 94.8kph, googly spinning down the leg-side, past Shankar's flick
Ravi Bishnoi to Shankar, 1 run, 100.9kph, punched to long-on

Highlights (6-10 overs) -> Yash Thakur bowls an inswinger to clean bowled Shubman -> Bishnoi takes a spectacular caught and bowled to remove Williamson -> Krunal bags his first wicket of the tournament in the form of Sudharsan -> Krunal gets his second wicket in the form of Sharath -> LSG spinners pull things back for the home team
Krunal Pandya to Shankar, 1 run, 83.8kph, bit of air but the length is on the shorter side, Shankar gets low to swat-pull it to deep backward square leg
Krunal Pandya to Darshan Nalkande, 1 run, 102.2kph, quicker one outside off from a short of length, punched to long-off
Krunal Pandya to Shankar, 1 run, 98kph, fuller ball drifting in on the sticks, Shankar drives along the carpet to long-on
Krunal Pandya to Darshan Nalkande, no run, 82.2kph, flighted delivery, Darshan Nalkande defends forward
Krunal Pandya to Darshan Nalkande, 1 run, 102.4kph, darted in around off, bunted to long-on
Krunal Pandya to Shankar, no run, 83.7kph, spinning away from a length, Shankar cuts hard off the back foot and QdK makes a superb stop with a dive to his right at extra cover
The required run rate is now in excess of 10 RPO
Manimaran Siddharth [3.0-0-20-0] is back into the attack
M Siddharth to Darshan Nalkande, no run, 96.1kph, full marginally outside off, pushed back to Siddharth
M Siddharth to Darshan Nalkande, SIX, 94.6kph, much-needed six for GT! Fullish on the sticks, Darshan Nalkande makes room, gets low and swings his willow hard to bludgeon it over the bowler's head
M Siddharth to Darshan Nalkande, 1 run, 99.4kph, Siddharth pulls his length back and that's been punched to long-on
M Siddharth to Shankar, no run, 97.2kph, Shankar looks to work this length ball into the leg-side and gets a leading edge that rolls back to Siddharth
M Siddharth to Shankar, 1 run, 100.1kph, uses the bowler's angle to turn it to midwicket
M Siddharth to Darshan Nalkande, 1 run, 101.1kph, fuller ball around leg, Darshan Nalkande slightly backs away to ease it to long-on. Siddharth finishes with 0/29!
Equation: 84 runs | 48 balls.
Krunal Pandya to Darshan Nalkande, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Krunal Pandya to Darshan Nalkande, out Caught by Yash Thakur!! Third wicket for Pandya! 99.1kph, not a good ball by any means but he gets a wicket. Fired down leg, Nalkande flicks it straight to short fine leg where Yash Thakur crouches low to reverse-cup it. GT have now lost half their side. Darshan Nalkande c Yash Thakur b Krunal Pandya 12(11) [6s-1]
Rahul Tewatia, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Krunal Pandya to Rahul Tewatia, no run, 82.6kph, flighted delivery drifting across the left-hander outside off, Rahul Tewatia can't lay bat on ball
Krunal Pandya to Rahul Tewatia, 1 run, worked through midwicket and Rahul Tewatia gets off the mark with a single
Krunal Pandya to Shankar, 1 run, 88.6kph, pad-lined, whipped away to deep backward square leg off the back foot
Krunal Pandya to Rahul Tewatia, no run, 91.7kph, fired on the pads, Tewatia looks to play it fine but doesn't connect. The ball rolls to short fine off his pad

Krunal Pandya to Rahul Tewatia, no run, 81.6kph, much slower to end the over and Rahul Tewatia didn't see that coming. Plays early at it and is beaten on the outside edge. Outstanding bowling performance from Krunal Pandya who finishes with 4-0-11-3!
Equation: 82 runs | 42 balls.
Naveen-ul-Haq [1.0-0-13-0] is back into the attack

Naveen-ul-Haq to Shankar, no run, 134.4kph, fuller than a length, Shankar drives hard but straight back at the bowler who deflects it towards cover. Replays show that the ball hit the bowler's chest after bouncing once
Naveen-ul-Haq to Shankar, 1 run, short outside off, pulled to long-on
Naveen-ul-Haq to Rahul Tewatia, 1 run, 115.4kph, pace off and short, Rahul Tewatia swivels to pull and is a bit early into his shot. Looked to place it squarer but the ball goes to deep midwicket

Naveen-ul-Haq to Shankar, SIX, cracking sound! 112.7kph, pace off and into the deck, Shankar sees that coming. Waits for it, clears his front leg and dispatches it into the midwicket stands with a powerful pull shot
Pooran has a word with the bowler and there's a change in the field. Third man and fine leg inside the circle
Naveen-ul-Haq to Shankar, 1 run, 137.4kph, yorker length, squeeze-driven towards mid-off and Pooran makes a diving stop to his right after running across from extra cover
Naveen-ul-Haq to Rahul Tewatia, 1 run, 135.1kph, shortish ball, short-arm-jabbed to deep midwicket

Timeout! GT slipped from 54/0 to 80/5 and the asking rate is now 12 RPO. Mayank Yadav left the field earlier with a side strain, not sure if he'll bowl again today. LSG have other bowling options though. The hosts are the favourites at this stage, let's find out if GT can pull off something special from here...
Yash Thakur [1.0-0-7-1] is back into the attack
Yash Thakur to Rahul Tewatia, leg byes 1 run, 134kph, round the wicket, Tewatia walks across to flick and inside-edges to backward square leg
Yash Thakur to Shankar, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Yash Thakur to Shankar, out Caught by Rahul!! Edged and gone! 133.8kph, short and wide outside off, Shankar hops and flashes his bat hard to flay it over backward point. All he manages is an audible edge that's been pouched by the keeper. Shankar c Rahul b Yash Thakur 17(17) [6s-1]
Rashid Khan, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Yash Thakur to Rashid Khan, no run, 138.1kph, skiddy length ball on off, Rashid Khan stays leg-side of the ball to tap it to backward point
Yash Thakur to Rashid Khan, no run, banged in short, good lift, Rashid Khan arches back to ramp it over the keeper but gets beaten for pace
Yash Thakur to Rashid Khan, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Yash Thakur to Rashid Khan, out Caught by (sub)Hooda!! Another one bites the dust! 117.3kph, slower ball on a short of a good length, Rashid Khan shimmies down the track in an attempt to slap it over the off-side. He's early into his shot and ends up toe-ending it towards mid-off where Hooda back-pedals and takes a comfortable catch. Three wickets in 11 balls for Yash Thakur! Rashid Khan c (sub)Hooda b Yash Thakur 0(3)
A slip in place
Umesh Yadav, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Yash Thakur to Umesh Yadav, no run, 138.9kph, length ball on off, Umesh Yadav defends it into the off-side and there's a I0$ between the batters. Eventually they decide against the single. Double wicket maiden from Yash Thakur!

Highlights (11-15 overs) -> Krunal bowls an economical over, concedes only four runs -> Siddharth proves to be slightly expensive in the 12th over -> Pandya bags this third wicket in the form of Nalkande -> Shankar strikes a clean six against Naveen in the 14th over -> Thakur removes Shankar and Rashid, bowls a double wicket maiden
Equation: 71 runs | 30 balls.
Naveen-ul-Haq to Rahul Tewatia, 1 run, 117.7kph, slow and short, Rahul Tewatia gets inside the line to pull it to fine leg
Naveen-ul-Haq to Umesh Yadav, 1 run, 134.7kph, in-angling bouncer from wide of the crease, Umesh hurriedly pulls and the ball falls short and wide of deep backward square leg
Naveen-ul-Haq to Rahul Tewatia, 1 run, 131.1kph, pulled to deep midwicket
Naveen-ul-Haq to Umesh Yadav, 1 run, 117.9kph, slower ball bouncer, pulled to deep midwicket
Naveen-ul-Haq to Rahul Tewatia, wide, 138.8kph, full and down leg from round the wicket, goes past Tewatia's attempted flick

Naveen-ul-Haq to Rahul Tewatia, no ball, 2 runs, 133.4kph, full outside off, Tewatia throws the kitchen sink and slices it over extra cover. Bishnoi runs back and does a superb job to flick it back into play. Saves two but Naveen-ul-Haq has overstepped
Naveen-ul-Haq to Rahul Tewatia, 1 run, 112.9kph, slower ball, Tewatia swings hard but mishits to long-on. Just a single off the free-hit
Naveen-ul-Haq to Umesh Yadav, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Naveen-ul-Haq to Umesh Yadav, out Caught by de Kock!! Naveen-ul-Haq joins the party! 113.1kph, slower ball on a fullish length and Umesh Yadav shapes to slog it over midwicket. Swings hard but the bat turns at the point of impact. More height than distance. QdK comes in from long-on, settles under the skier and calmly catches it. Umesh Yadav c de Kock b Naveen-ul-Haq 2(4)
Equation: 62 runs | 24 balls.
Spencer Johnson, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Yash Thakur to Rahul Tewatia, SIX, 135.1kph, just over deep backward square leg. Short of length ball, Tewatia walks across and stays back to slug it behind square on the leg-side. Siddharth goes for a one-handed catch with a jump but the ball is just out of his reach
Yash Thakur to Rahul Tewatia, no run, 136.9kph, over the wicket now and Yash Thakur bowls a back of a length delivery, patted towards extra cover and the batters don't take the single

Yash Thakur to Rahul Tewatia, FOUR, 123.8kph, pace off and short, Rahul Tewatia gets inside the line to swivel-pull. Naveen-ul-Haq runs to his right from long-on to try and push the ball back into play but makes a mess of it. Yash Thakur isn't happy with that effort
Yash Thakur to Rahul Tewatia, wide, 131.4kph, tries to bowl outside Tewatia's arc and ends up bowling too wide outside off
Yash Thakur to Rahul Tewatia, no run, 118.7kph, off-speed fullish ball, Tewatia swings hard but miscues it towards mid-on
Rahul Tewatia has a word with the umpire, probably some disturbance near the sightscreen

Yash Thakur to Rahul Tewatia, wide, 136.2kph, banged in short and Rahul Tewatia misses the pull after moving across. Wided for height, a late call from the square leg umpire. Tewatia signalled T even before that but the TV umpire won't be summoned
Yash Thakur to Rahul Tewatia, 1 run, 136.4kph, shimmies down the track and flicks to deep midwicket
Yash Thakur to Spencer Johnson, no run, 133.7kph, in-slanter following a backing away batter. Johnson is late to bring his bat down and the ball thuds into his pads
Equation: 49 runs | 18 balls. Bishnoi may have to bowl one over. Naveen-ul-Haq to bowl his final over...
Naveen-ul-Haq to Rahul Tewatia, no run, 133.9kph, short ball, pulled to deep backward square leg, single not taken
Naveen-ul-Haq to Rahul Tewatia, no run, 112.5kph, slower ball, Tewatia is early into his pull shot and doesn't connect. Rahul claps
Naveen-ul-Haq to Rahul Tewatia, no run, 114.9kph, pace off again, pulled towards deep backward square leg
Naveen-ul-Haq to Rahul Tewatia, no run, 107.8kph, off-speed again, fuller in length, drilled straight back at the bowler
Naveen-ul-Haq to Rahul Tewatia, FOUR, finds the gap now. 114.9kph, short ball, Tewatia fetches from outside off and pulls fiercely through square leg
Naveen-ul-Haq to Rahul Tewatia, 1 run, 115.8kph, short again, Tewatia pulls along the ground to deep midwicket to keep the strike
Equation: 44 runs | 12 balls. Yash Thakur to bowl the penultimate over.
Yash Thakur to Rahul Tewatia, no run, 138.6kph, full on the pads, flicked to deep backward square leg
Yash Thakur to Rahul Tewatia, SIX, 122.9kph, slow, full and in the slot, Rahul Tewatia gets down low to flog it over deep midwicket for an 80m six. Rahul isn't happy with that delivery
Yash Thakur to Rahul Tewatia, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Yash Thakur to Rahul Tewatia, out Caught by Pooran!! Holes out! 124.5kph, Yash Thakur pulls his length back, Tewatia pulls it flat and straight to deep square leg. Couldn't generate much power behind it and didn't get the elevation as wel. Pooran doesn't err and that's wicket number four for Yash Thakur. Rahul Tewatia c Pooran b Yash Thakur 30(25) [4s-2 6s-2]
Can Yash Thakur get a fifer?
Noor Ahmad, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Yash Thakur to Noor Ahmad, FOUR, 125.2kph, almost! Bouncer into the deck, Noor Ahmad looks to glide it and gets some wood and the ball just manages to elude the jumping Rahul
Yash Thakur to Noor Ahmad, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Yash Thakur to Noor Ahmad, out Caught by de Kock!! Fifer for Yash Thakur and LSG win by 33 runs! 133.7kph, pace on and banged into the wicket, Noor stays leg-side to pull and top-edges it straight to de Kock at mid-on. Yash Thakur has his arms aloft and Bishnoi is the first one to hug him. Noor Ahmad c de Kock b Yash Thakur 4(2) [4s-1]

23:12 Local Time, 17:42 GMT, 23:12 IST: Convincing win for the hosts! At the halfway stage most of us thought that 163 was under-par. But LSG find ways to defend totals if their batters post totals in excess of 160. Mind you, GT got off to a brisk start as well with the bat. In Saha's absence Sai Sudharsan opened the innings with Gill and the stylish left-hander was quick to get off the blocks. They forged the first 50-plus opening stand for the Titans this season with Sudharsan being the aggressor. Naveen-ul-Haq conceded a couple of fours off his first over, Mayank Yadav leaked three boundaries off his opening over. And, then Siddharth bowled three front-foot no-balls in an over after a couple of tight overs. It was Yash Thakur who provided the breakthrough for LSG as he castled the GT captain with a pacy full ball off the final ball of the powerplay. That opened the floodgates. KL Rahul turned to his experienced spinners and they delivered tonight. Bishnoi took a screamer off his own bowling to remove KW and Krunal Pandya varied his pace smartly to pick a three-fer. The Titans slipped from 54/0 to 80/5 and they couldn't recover from it. Thakur, who started it all, came back to finish with impressive figures of 5/30. He stepped up for his team after Mayank Yadav left the field with a side strain.

Shubman Gill | GT captain: It was a good wicket to bat on, a poor batting performance by us. We got a decent start, but we lost wickets in the middle and couldn't recover from that. Our bowlers were exceptional as they restricted them to 160-odd, just that our batters let us down. (On missing David Miller) Miller is a kind of a player who can change a game in a couple of overs, because I think this total was very gettable for us. (On his dismissal) I thought it was the last over of the powerplay and I just wanted to make the most of it, just that I missed that ball as I tried to play a bit too square. It was tremendous to watch our bowlers bowl, we were looking forward to restricting them around 160-165.

Krunal Pandya: When I went in, I played a couple of balls, I had a chat with Pooran as well, the wicket was very good. We felt that we were 10-15 short but at the end of the day, that's what we got, so we had to defend. I like to know the batters' strengths and weaknesses, try to bowl according to it. It comes off some days and it doesn't some days. I back my strengths and stuck to my plans, one of those days I executed what I wanted, tonight it came off. It feels great to defend this score, the way we have defended even last year. [on Mayank Yadav] I don't know what is happening, but I had a couple of seconds with him, he seems OK. He is a bright prospect, bowled gun in the nets, last year missed out. Good head on his shoulders and unbelievable prospect and interesting to see how he will pan out in his career.

KL Rahul | LSG captain: We'll take the win, I am not going to make too much out of it (on defending totals). For the young bowling unit we have, it helps when we bat first. They get an idea how the wicket is playing and they've also been adapting really well. It's a good record to have (defending all 160+ totals), but it's also where we've played. Having the home advantage helps. The bowlers have come through the ranks over the last couple of years. you have seen the same guys bowling in the last season as well., They have adjusted to their roles. Hopefully we can continue this. We knew that it wasn't as good as the wicket we played on (in the previous match here), also losing two wickets in the powerplay will set us back a bit. Unless someone carries on to get 70-80, it was tough to achieve that 170-180. We just wanted to bat and see how much we can get. That's the advantage you have when you are batting first. All three spinners have been key for us. Sid coming in this season has done really well, he plays a crucial part with the new ball, he's shown great temperament. His job is to restrict the batters. KP (Krunal Pandya) is very experienced, he's played IPL for so many seasons. Bishnoi has been around for so many years and keeps getting better. Feels good to get off the mark there (first win vs GT).

Yash Thakur | Player of the Match (translated from Hindi): Happy with this five-wicket haul and Man of the Match award. I had planned against Gill, I stuck to my plan, KL Rahul had advised me to do so and it paid off. Unfortunately Mayank Yadav got injured, so KL said it was my day and asked me to make the most of it. We are winning the first game against GT in IPL history, very happy with it. Really enjoyed Gill's wicket, the most memorable of all.

Mumbai Indians, earlier today, got off the mark in a high-scoring encounter against Delhi. Here in Lucknow, it was an even contest between bat and ball. Hat-trick of wins for LSG and they climb up to the third spot with this 33-run win. Gujarat, on the other hand, have now lost two on the bounce. That's it for today. Tune in tomorrow for I0$.
